com.tinkerpop.blueprints

Interface Element

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Edge, Vertex
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventEdge, EventElement, EventVertex, IdEdge, IdElement, IdVertex, Neo4jEdge, Neo4jVertex, OrientEdge, OrientElement, OrientVertex, PartitionEdge, PartitionElement, PartitionVertex, ReadOnlyEdge, ReadOnlyVertex, RexsterEdge, RexsterVertex, SailEdge, SailVertex, WrappedEdge, WrappedElement, WrappedVertex

    public interface Element
    An Element is the base class for both vertices and edges. An element has an identifier that must be unique to its inheriting classes (vertex or edges). An element can maintain a collection of key/value properties. Keys are always Strings and values can be any Object. Particular implementations can reduce the space of objects that can be used as values. Typically, objects are Java primitives (e.g. String, long, int, boolean, etc.)
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)
